public interface Claim<T>

Claim interface. A claim is a piece of information about an entity that a claims provider asserts about that entity.

A claim has a canonical name and a value that serialises to a JSON boolean, string, number, array, object or null.

Claims are typically serialised into a JSON object: 

 {
   "user_id"  : 123456789,
   "name"     : "Alice Wonderland",
   "email"    : "alice@wonderland.net",
   "verified" : true,
   "locales"  : ["en", "en-GB"],
 }

Version:
0.9 (2012-05-16)
Author:
